                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/216a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 14, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. Representatives of Standard-Vacuum called at Department on November 6 in
                    regard to oil situation in Japan and stated that a conference was scheduled for
                    that day between officials of the Japanese Foreign Office and Department of
                    Commerce and Industry and representatives of foreign oil interests.</p>
                <p>Did such conference take place and if so what were the results?</p>
                <p>Please telegraph reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
